I think the ORIENT was the flagship for the Anniversary Day Regatta in <b>1884</b>.  Was this the big occasion?

&quot;To-day the R.M.S. Orient is to be moved from the Circular Quay to Farm Cove, where she will be the flagship at the Anniversary Regatta. She will be moored to the Nelson's buoy. &quot; 
